WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.060
All right. So I was tasked today to present our data, our institutional data on lancastuximab

00:00:08.060 --> 00:00:13.560
with rituximab in patients with relapsed refractory follicular lymphoma.

00:00:14.580 --> 00:00:20.200
So as a background, frontline therapy for follicular lymphoma is well-defined.

00:00:20.900 --> 00:00:26.420
The standard approach in the relapse setting is less so, although that's probably changing

00:00:26.420 --> 00:00:29.260
with the recent approval of epicaritamab.

00:00:30.160 --> 00:00:36.020
Lancastuximab-tucerin is an antibody drug conjugate comprising a humanized anti-CD19

00:00:36.020 --> 00:00:41.260
antibody, which is conjugated to tucerin, an alkylating agent.

00:00:42.080 --> 00:00:48.040
In the initial phase one study of lancastuximab, the drug demonstrated an overall response

00:00:48.040 --> 00:00:52.100
rate of 78% and a complete response of 64%.

00:00:52.100 --> 00:00:56.220
So we conducted a phase two study investigating this.

00:00:56.420 --> 00:01:02.400
So this is the study schema.

00:01:02.400 --> 00:01:08.340
We included patients with follicular lymphoma meeting the GELF criteria for treatment in

00:01:08.340 --> 00:01:15.540
addition to POD24 and patients having their second and beyond relapse.

00:01:16.100 --> 00:01:22.220
The treatment schema includes lancastuximab given every three weeks in an induction period

00:01:22.220 --> 00:01:23.740
combined with rituximab.

00:01:24.200 --> 00:01:25.360
And after 12 weeks, we included lancastuximab.

00:01:25.360 --> 00:01:25.960
So we included lancastuximab given every three weeks in an induction period combined with rituximab.

00:01:25.960 --> 00:01:25.960
And after 12 weeks, we included lancastuximab given every three weeks in an induction period combined with rituximab.

00:01:25.960 --> 00:01:25.960
And after 12 weeks, we included lancastuximab given every three weeks in an induction period combined with rituximab.

00:01:25.960 --> 00:01:25.960
And after 12 weeks, we included lancastuximab given every three weeks in an induction period combined with rituximab.

00:01:25.960 --> 00:01:26.440
And after 12 weeks, we included lancastuximab given every three weeks in an induction period combined with rituximab.

00:01:26.440 --> 00:01:26.500
And after 12 weeks, we included lancastuximab given every three weeks in an induction period combined with rituximab.

00:01:26.500 --> 00:01:32.520
PET-CTs are done, and that defines the primary outcome of CR at 12 weeks.

00:01:33.040 --> 00:01:37.420
Subsequently, patients achieving a response get a maintenance phase,

00:01:37.840 --> 00:01:42.420
followed by extended maintenance phase if they continue to have a response.

00:01:42.860 --> 00:01:45.440
For patients with CR, they got rituximab alone.

00:01:45.580 --> 00:01:49.860
For patients with partial response, they completed on lancastuximab.

00:01:50.020 --> 00:01:53.680
The total treatment is less than 10 months.

00:01:54.020 --> 00:01:55.940
So the median follow-up for this study is that,

00:01:55.960 --> 00:01:58.680
this study that I'm presenting today is 18 months.

00:01:59.240 --> 00:02:04.660
And as I mentioned, the primary outcome is CR at 30 months.

00:02:05.620 --> 00:02:09.600
So baseline characteristics, looking at this patient population,

00:02:10.120 --> 00:02:16.460
there were about 30% of those patients having prior transformed disease and grade 3A as well.

00:02:17.440 --> 00:02:22.920
Looking at the Flippy score, more than 60% had high Flippy score,

00:02:22.920 --> 00:02:25.920
and POT24 represented half of those.

00:02:25.960 --> 00:02:29.060
So that's a lot more than the average population.

00:02:29.060 --> 00:02:31.840
High tumor burden by the GALF criteria was more than 90%.

00:02:31.840 --> 00:02:36.080
So that was the main inclusion criteria that was met.

00:02:38.580 --> 00:02:40.600
Looking at the side effect profile,

00:02:41.300 --> 00:02:47.440
cytopenia, specifically neutropenia and lymphopenia were grade 3 and above,

00:02:47.440 --> 00:02:50.720
were present in more than 10% of patients.

00:02:51.460 --> 00:02:55.240
Additionally, some unique side effects for lancastuximab,

00:02:55.240 --> 00:02:55.740
the RAP.

00:02:55.740 --> 00:03:00.740
The rash and the photosensitivity were grade 1 and 2 mostly,

00:03:00.740 --> 00:03:06.540
and were present in 35% and 15% of the population, respectively.

00:03:06.540 --> 00:03:09.980
A third spacing can occur in lancastuximab.

00:03:09.980 --> 00:03:15.540
So pleural effusion grade 1 and 2 were reported in about 12% of patients.

00:03:17.940 --> 00:03:21.000
This is the primary outcome.

00:03:21.000 --> 00:03:25.520
So at week 12, the overall response rate was 97.4.

00:03:25.520 --> 00:03:31.940
And the CR rate was 66.7% for the overall population.

00:03:31.940 --> 00:03:38.840
When looking at best response, this improved with the CR rate reaching 76.9%.

00:03:38.840 --> 00:03:46.700
Looking at high-risk groups within follicular lymphoma,

00:03:46.700 --> 00:03:53.300
we see that lancastuximab achieves very high overall response rates and CR rates

00:03:53.300 --> 00:03:55.300
across the different risk groups.

00:03:55.300 --> 00:04:01.540
So looking at POT24, high-risk Flippy score and prior transformed follicular lymphoma

00:04:01.540 --> 00:04:10.060
and double refractory patients, they all had very similar outcomes with overall response

00:04:10.060 --> 00:04:16.380
rates approaching 90 and 100%.

00:04:16.380 --> 00:04:25.080
Looking at the survival curves at 12 months, the progression-free survival was 94.6%.

00:04:25.080 --> 00:04:31.240
The overall survival was also 94.1%.

00:04:31.240 --> 00:04:35.200
And that was at 12 months.

00:04:35.200 --> 00:04:42.320
So building on this, we are expanding this IIT to be in multiple centers across the United

00:04:42.320 --> 00:04:43.320
States.

00:04:43.320 --> 00:04:49.880
And we are also adjusting the schedule so patients will finish the whole treatment in

00:04:49.880 --> 00:04:54.860
less than five months, basically, if they achieve a CR or PR at week 12.

00:04:54.860 --> 00:05:01.720
Those patients are receiving two additional doses of lancastuximab and rituximab and complete

00:05:01.720 --> 00:05:03.120
study at that point.

00:05:03.120 --> 00:05:11.600
We're also going to be measuring ctDNA throughout different time points as well.

00:05:11.600 --> 00:05:17.920
So as a conclusion, limited duration lancastuximab and rituximab drive significant CR rate in

00:05:17.920 --> 00:05:22.040
the second line and later follicular lymphoma.

00:05:22.040 --> 00:05:24.640
This study met its primary endpoint with a week 12.

00:05:24.640 --> 00:05:37.060
And the CR appeared to be prolonged, our 12-month PFS of 94.6% validates that and not reaching

00:05:37.060 --> 00:05:40.200
the median PFS.

00:05:40.200 --> 00:05:45.060
The safety profile within follicular lymphoma is consistent with prior studies in large

00:05:45.060 --> 00:05:46.980
B-cell lymphoma.

00:05:46.980 --> 00:05:52.760
Most adverse events were grade 1 and 2, so they were low grade, including hyperglycemia

00:05:52.760 --> 00:05:54.420
and elevated liver enzymes.

00:05:54.420 --> 00:05:56.600
In the second line, we saw a decrease in the amount of lancastuximab and rituximab, and

00:05:56.600 --> 00:05:57.600
a decrease in the amount of C-cell lymphoma.

00:05:57.600 --> 00:06:01.360
So this study suggests that fixed-duration program of lancastuximab with rituximab is

00:06:01.360 --> 00:06:05.200
a promising combination in the second line and beyond.

00:06:05.200 --> 00:06:11.220
So I'd like to thank everyone within our group in the lymphoma and acknowledge the PI of this

00:06:11.220 --> 00:06:16.380
study, Dr. Alderuccio, and our lymphoma section chief, Dr. Isidore Losos.

00:06:16.380 --> 00:06:17.180
Thank you.
